_json.gridTitle: Why One Girl Has to Guzzle 8 Bottles of Powerade a Day
_json.description: COSMOPOLITAN magazine~"A condition called Dysautonomia. This dysfunction of my autonomic nervous system messed with everything from my circulation and blood pressure to my body temperature, kidneys, heart, bladder, and intestinal tract. P.O.T.S. or Postural Orthostatic Tachycardia Syndrome was the end-stage of Dysautonomia. With so many diverse symptoms affecting so many different organ systems—until it hits your heart—you could go your entire life without being diagnosed."
